column3: Предимството на плажа е, че покрай бреговете му почти няма вълни. Дори при силен вятър по-крайбрежието рядко има вълни с височина по-голяма от 20-30 сантиметра. Прекрасно е за плуване в такива тихи води.
Хубав плаж. Дълъг е около 10 км.  Идеален е за разходки по и около него.
Многолюден плаж. Приятна за разходки променада.

The beaches in Marmaris Downtown are not the greatest in the world but are more than adequate for children and adults alike. The sand is mostly black sand and a bit gritty. The beaches are not very wide and the top half is covered in sunbeds and umbrellas which you can rent for a nominal fee if the hotel/restaurant does not provide them.

Плажа е защитен от морските течения с брегоукрепителни съоръжения, които го правят тих и спокоен през целия летен сезон. Пясъчната ивица е сравнително тясна и още в ранните часове на деня се препълва от летовници. Полегатото му дъно го прави безопасен за игра на деца в морето.
Very nice beach, sheltered by sea waves. Suitable for swimming, running and walking along the coast. Excellent location.
Not the most spectacular beach I've been to. If you want to avoid the crowds, be sure to be there early in the morning.

Many people on the beach. Dozens of jets in the sea water. Cars on the beach move in the evening. Too noisy beach. Cloudy seawater. Unpleasant to bath. Wonderful sunsets.

This beach is at the very beginning of the Sunny Day 2-kilometer-long beach. There are plenty of rocks, and the sand isn't that good. On top of that, the mineral water pipe is very close nearby, so it isn't very clean.

One of my favorite beaches in Sharm El Sheikh. Protected by predominant winds. Rarely there are waves here. Maybe 1-2 times in 10 days. Coral reef right in front of the beach is nothing special. To the left of the beach, however, towards Ras Um Um Sid Bai, the coral reef is wonderful. The average height of the coral wall varies from 2 to 8-10-12 m. The seabed after the coral wall is mostly sandy. A wonderful snorkeling spot.

Good beach for sunbathing. Coral reef in front of him is very poor .. For water I recommend beach shoes There is security at the entrance. Access is limited. At the moment there are repairs on the beach.

Great place for snorkeling and swimming. Affordable wonderful coral reef. Diverse underwater life. Here you can find fish lion, parrot fish, picasso fish, mint, skate, moraine and various corals. The stairs to the beach are a bit steep, but they are not a problem.

The beach is protected by the prevailing winds. It is very rare to see a light sea wave here. Guaranteed at least 25 days a month here the sea has a flat surface. The beach is divided into two parts. The northern part is only for the guests of the nearby hotel-Beach Albatross. External people are not allowed. The southern part is a public beach with free access. There is a security guard. It is sad that this pretty beach is never cleaned. The beach is dirty. The sand is also very bad. But sea water is clean. Coral reef is also very good. The coral wall is only 2-3-4 meters tall. Below the wall, the bottom is almost everywhere with beautiful sand. A wonderful snorkeling spot. Very suitable for people who are beginners - swimmers and snorkellers.

The most frequently photographed beach, which has become the emblem of Sharm El Sheikh. The other name on the beach is Golden Beach. Few are Sharm beaches with fine sand and this is one of them. The best sand is in front of Faraana Reef Resort and Reef Oasis Beach Resort. Ras Um Sid Bay is protected from the prevailing winds. Even in the winter months there are rarely sea waves. The coral reef in the bay is wonderful. Since the bay and the coral reef are large, there are sections with better and more opaque corals. The best coral formations are in the western part of the bay, in the direction of Ras Katy Beach. The bay is perfect for snorkeling by beginners. Depth is small. An average of 4-8 meters. There are almost no currents, or very weak. Coral and sand islands are often routed along the seabed. The marine fauna here is also abundant. All of this creates a wonderful feeling for anyone entering this paradise aquarium.
A crowded beach. Music, beach games, water aerobics and great snorkeling. Something for everyone.

Very well-sheltered bay. Almost always quiet and without the sea waves. Minus is that there is no coral reef. There are several crowded public beaches here-(Terrazzina, El Kheima etc). The water in this relatively closed bay with a narrow mouth is unfortunately quite polluted. The bottom is slimy.

Wind-protected bay. No waves. Good sand. Sandy seabed. Suitable for young children. Pretty crowded beach. It is well cleaned mainly in the adjacent hotels-Iberotel Palace and Dessole Seti Sharm Resort. For private tourists there are several private beaches with restaurants and a paid entrance. Public Beach-Google Maps Coordinates: 27.861129, 34.297207;    El Kheima Beach- Google Maps Coordinates: 27.862679, 34.291397;    Terazina Beach -Google Maps Coordinates: 27.859912, 34.289498 .... From Maya Bay Beach go the boats with which tourists explore the nearby coral reefs. http://www.unitedsubmarines.com/ What the tourists see underwater with these boats can also be explored independently, if a snorkeling is made along Wild Beach-Hadaba and Ras Katy Beach.

Perfect beach for snorkelling and diving directly from the shore. A high coral wall-20-30м. Due to the considerable depth, the bottom is often lost sight. The marine fauna here is abundant. Often there is a sea current changing its direction.

Access to Palma Beach is limited. It is used only by the guests of several hotels, among them Falcon Hills Hotel. The beach area is quite large. There are plenty of umbrellas and deck chairs that lie on something that can hardly be called sand. The real sandy beach is small, with good sand. Just in front of this little sandy beach is the pontoon that leads to the coral wall. The coral wall is 20-25 meters high. In some places the bottom is lost from sight while swimming over the water. A lot of people here can experience fear of depth. Coral reef good. With dozens of species of coral and marine fauna. The snorkeling here, however, quickly gets tired because it swims around a nearly identical coral wall everywhere. The sea current, which is almost constant, with varying speed and direction, should not be neglected. Most of the eastern winds blowing wind winds blow here. Perhaps 7-8 every 10 days the winds are. On such days, snorkeling is not pleasant here. The strategy is to watch the direction of the wind. When the wind blows the winds here is perfect. .... Coral reef and snorkeling conditions are similar to and in front of the beaches of the two adjoining hotels - Renaissance Sharm El Sheikh Golden View Beach Resort and Sunrise Grand Select Montemare Resort.

The most visited beach of Starm El Sheikh. Protected by winds. Very good quality of the sand. Well maintained, especially in front of the best beachfront hotels, like Fayrouz Resort, Sharm El Sheikh Marriott Resort and Novotel Hotel Naama Bay. Child-friendly beach. Mostly sandy seabed. There are coral areas in separate places. The quality of the coral reefs here is very low. Still, a decent snorkeling can be done. Sometimes the cleanliness of sea water here is surprisingly good for a crowded beach. From time to time, however, seawater may be unpleasantly dirty. Public Beach - Cheapest-10 EGP, 0,6 USD (2017) Google Maps Coordinates: 27.912458, 34.328016 ----- Delta Sharm Beach - 40 EGP, 2,3 USD (2017) Google Maps Coordinates: 27.913970, 34.330982

Access to the beaches of Mövenpick Resort Sharm el Sheikh is limited to outside guests. Access to the coral reef by sea, however, has no one to restrict. With a small swim from the northern beach of Naama Bay, it is easy to get here. Here is the best coral reef in the whole bay. The seabed is a mixture of coral gardens and sandy areas. Average depth: from 2 to 7 m. A nice snorkeling spot.

Montazah Public Beach is one of the most pleasant beaches of Sharm El Sheikh. The sand is very good. Something rare in Sharm. Here are very few people. It's calm. In front of the beach is Ras bob coral reef. Excellent coral reef!!! One of the best places in Sharm El Sheikh for snorkeling. You have to go through the reef plate (0.5м) to get to the reef wall. The height of the reef wall varies from 3 to 10-12 meters. Below the reef wall there is a sandy slope dotted with various coral formations. Mostly coral gardens with pinnacles. Often, there are weak currents parallel to the shore that change their direction.

Good beach for sunbathing. The Coral Reef is near the coast. Very different corals and a diverse marine world.There is a slight current. Excellent snorkeling. The place is a villa area. There are many construction projects at the moment. There are no grocery stores. The closest are to Naama Bay.

An impressive desert beach. People rarely come here. These are mostly people who have pedestrian access from the nearby two hotels: Hyatt Regency Sharm El Sheikh Resort  and Mövenpick Resort Sharm el Sheikh. Good swimmers can get to this beach by Naama Bay. Good coral reef in front of the beach - "Near Garden Reef". Good snorkeling, but nothing special.

Wonderful, wild, hard-to-reach beach. It is about 4 km long. Only 1/3 of it is accessible by cars on a narrow mountain road.

Kayaking is wonderful outside the rocky shield, though it could get dangerous.

Wonderful place - spacious, windy with clean sea water. The beach, away from the noise of the big cities, is a great place to relax. There is a campsite near it which offers accommodation, parking and food for its visitors.

The endless beach and wildlife. Even at the height of summer, this paradise remains untouched by crowds, and every beachfriend can indulge in peace and quiet. This is one of the most beautiful places on the Bulgarian Black Sea coast. On the northern beaches in Bulgaria, a strong wind blows and it is a great condition for kitesurfers.

The beach at the Dobrudja campsite in Shabla is clean and spacious, there is plenty of space for every visitor. Here is definitely the atmosphere of the northernmost beaches along the Bulgarian Black Sea coast. Visitors to the place can enjoy the endless horizon, both on land and by sea.

Kabakum Beach is one of the most visited beaches in Varna. Many of them have cottages in the area or choose it because of the cheap restaurants and the many attractions, including water bicycles, jets and more. The beach has free parking.

I avoid this beach when I can. You never know when there's going to be 'stuff' swimming in the water, especially near the pier. Parking there is an absolute nightmare during the season. To top it off, it's extremely crowded.
I wouldn't recommend this beach at all. Always full of people, and you get the feeling all of the dirty water converges there.
A good looking city beach, but the sea water here is not clean.
A typical city beach, but the sea water here is not very clean. Behind the beach there is a lovely city park about 4 km long. A wonderful place to go for a walk.

This is where nightlife is in the summer. Plenty of bars/discos, and tons of young people. That being said, it's dirty and noisy, so not everyone's cup of tea.

Perhaps one of the best Coral Reef in Sharm El-Skaih. Perfect for snorkeling parallel to the coral wall all along the beach. For the weaker swimmers you can rest on the pontoons in front of each hotel. Current-mostly light. Often the current changes its direction. Best Coral Reef is in front of Coral Sea Sensatori Resort and Baron Resort-9,1/10. In the south, in front of a Coral Beach Montazah Hotel, the coral reef is a bit weaker- 8/10. The height of the reef wall varies from 5 to 10-12 meters. Below the reef wall there is Coral garden with pinnacles.

A great beach. The Coral Reef is near the coast. Very different corals and a diverse marine world. Excellent snorkeling. There is a slight current. There are several five star hotels in the area. It is close to the villa area of Sharm el-Sheikh

The beach is maintained by the Melton Beaches Resort. The Coral Reef is near the coast. Very different corals and a diverse marine world. Excellent snorkeling. There is a slight current. It is close to the villa area of Sharm el-Sheikh.

Easy access to the coral wall on the pontoon of the Melton Beach Resort. Very good coral reef. There are sections of dead coral. The sea current may be moderately strong with a changing direction. Around the pontoon is relatively protected by the prevailing northern winds and is pleasant for snorkeling. Ras Nasrani is a famous diving spot and here often stop boats with tourists for snorkelling and diving.

Wild beach. There are unfinished hotel buildings around. It's dirty everywhere on the beach. The lagoon is very shallow in front of the beach. Along the shore, entry into the water in most places is on the sand. After 5-10 meters, the sea bottom is dotted mainly with stones and small corals. It's not good for bathing in the water and snorkeling.

This amazing place combines the beauty of the wild and the seashore. Only a few meters from the sea stretches a thick forest where visitors often have their own tents. The beach of Irakli is long and wide. From the entrance, the sand is fine and yellow. The more southward to the village of Emona a man goes, the sand becomes bigger and gradually becomes gravel. Nearby there are restaurants where you can buy food and hot drinks. The beach is visited by nudists, who are mainly located in the southern part of the strip.
It's been a long time since I've last been there, so take this with a grain of salt. Very windy, with turbulent waters. Few people.
Amazing place.

Very nice beach surrounded by north and south with rocky shores and areas suitable for underwater fishing. The water is clean and the bottom is suitable for children

Lipite Beach is located near the village of Sinemorets. The beach is located in a beautiful, small bay, preserving beauty and wildlife. It is surrounded by beautiful hills and forest, making it a very attractive place. Next to it is a trail starting from the southern end of Butamyata Beach. There is also a road to a car, but if your car is not 4x4 you can save yourself this experience. In addition, visits by the Border Police and fines for parking on the territory of Strandja Park are possible. The road on foot is far healthier and is suitable for inexperienced tourists and children. It will take you twenty minutes to walk through the paths and get to Lipite beach. At the southern end of Butamia Beach you will see the paths that pass over the rocks. Lipite Beach is an amazing place. Small, sheltered between the trees with exceptionally clean and fine sand. Practically, these twenty minutes of passage refuse more lazy tourists and visitors to Lipite enjoy true tranquility and seclusion. Here are missing hotels and any buildings that disturb the beachmen.

If you have never seen a deer or deer in its natural environment, you will have the opportunity here. About 4 kilometers south of Sinemorets is Lisi Beach. It is only a short walk away, and the road runs along the goat's path along the coast. This makes it less visited by tourists and especially attractive for those of you who are looking for the ultimate seaside relaxation. It is about 400-500 meters long with slight breaks of rocks reaching the seawater.
One of the best beaches in Bulgaria.
Nice beach with wide beach. A seabed suitable for young children. In some places its bottom is covered with small round stones, which makes walking a bit awkward.

Nice beach with fine sand, well maintained and clean. It becomes a bit more turbulent to the sea, starts to throw away seaweed. The beach is quite shallow and suitable for children. In the bay is also the waves are small.
The beach is small and quite rocky. The bay is quiet and beautiful, for people who want to see the seabed and love to dive is wishful.
A small and very beautiful bay with a beach! A favorite place for many people. The result is - overcrowded beach. Purity is not supported at level. The water at sea is not very clean. Pretty algae.
Clean, calm and well-kept beach! Wide sandy beach. Offers opportunities for all kinds of tourists.

The beach is long and wide. There is a forest around it. There is both a guarded and unguarded beach. There is a school for water and extreme sports on the beach. There is a possibility of staying in a hotel and camping, or in a tent or camper.

The biggest and bustling beach in Lozenets. The spacious beach is covered with fine sand. This is the most visited and popular beach, favorite place for many tourists. Here you will find many pubs, bars, nightclubs, children's places, and surf school

The beach is wide and spacious but is often full of people. The sand is fine and relatively clean. Around the beach there are places to buy food and drinks. Overnight stays are available both in the campsite and in different hotels in the city and at the homes of people offering rooms for rent.

The beach is situated on a beautiful bay in the northern part of Kiten. The beach is extremely beautiful with fine golden sand and blue, warm seawater. It is surrounded by wooded vegetation. The bay is seldom excited. Around the beach there are many hotels, bungalows, restaurants. Minus is that during the active season, the beach is overcrowded.
A very long beach. Excellent for swimming/running. I've only been there off-season, though.
The beach is quite impressive. Its length is more than 2 km. He is filled with people in the summer. The sand is very clean.
Lovely beach. Pure sand. Amazing dunes.
It's quite a long beach. I always remember it windy, but it's bearable. The sand dunes are quite interesting. Quite suitable for running/swimming.
A nice long beach divided into two parts by a small rocky stretch and with majestic rocks behind it. The beach has a guy who is friendly.
Papaya Beach - beautiful, clean .... real tropical paradise.
A nice but often crowded beach. Here boats stop with picnic tourists.
The Karst Mountains rising behind Ipil Beach provide a dramatic backdrop to a beautiful white sand beach.
The beach is great, easily accessible if you rent a kayak and ... surprisingly deserted.
Terrible dirty beach, mostly in the northern part. Gradually going south makes it a little cleaner, it's generally miserable.

The beach sand at Isla Reta Beach Resort is fine and very nice. The shore is steep enough and there is no problem with access to water at low tide. The bottom of the shore is mostly sandy and the water is surprisingly clean despite the proximity of the resort to the Santa Kruz fishing village.

The Coral Garden here is located just off the coast. Just about 100-150 meters from the shores of Liposutan Beach and at a depth of 1 to 4 meters lies this incredibly beautiful coral garden. Corals here are certainly over 100 species, and fish even more species. There is no way to describe in words what lies beneath the water. An incredible variety of shapes, colors and species living in harmony. Some corals are stunningly large in size. This natural wealth is also very preserved. Rare corrupted by human hand is rare.

On the beach under the shadows of the palm trees is full of various fishing boats and here we are in some fishing house.
Sea water and beach. Almost perfect! Beautiful sand, a long beach, clean sea water, a lovely coral garden underwater full of life.
Perfect beach. Good for diving and jumping. The water is very clean.
Pure water, nice sand on the beach and in the water.
Super beautiful place! The beach is unique, small is overpopulated. The water is sky blue.
A small wild beach. In front of him one of the two best coral reefs in the area.

A small beautiful island. There are many boat tourists here to enjoy. Almost anywhere around the island there is a good coral reef suitable for snorkeling.

Nice beach with a view of Koh Phangan. However it's full of bars and restaurants, no intimacy and no getaway from the noise. This side of Samui is very touristy and expensive.

The beach of photos looks very good. Even impressive. However, the reality is slightly different. The campsite behind the beach has a very good infrastructure. It is suitably maintained by at least 25 people. In fact, some of them control the basic daily flow of tourists to various places in the national park, including the lake on the neighboring island and the organized kayaking. The problem with the campsite is that it is located just in a wider gully, in the middle of which runs a small creek. Visibly, the water from the baths flows into this river, and it is in the sea of ​​the beach where the tourists have organized ... snorkeling. Waste water from the toilets and restaurants quite hidden, but understandably also fall into the sea. It happens that the currents in a strange way do not treat these dirt somewhere in the broad sea, but they stay at the northern end of the beach. As a result, a small stinking pond is formed along the coast at one end of the beach, and water in the sea can be described as tragically unpleasant. On a picture, however, the beach looks incredibly well and is a perfect lure for tourists.

The beach is radically different in high tide and at low tide. At high tide it is wonderful to swim in the bay. At a low tide, you need to walk about 400 meters to get a good swim depth. The Coral Reef is about 500 meters from the shore.
Average quality snorkeling. Coral reef is easily accessible from Mae Ngam Beach.

The beaches around the Turtle Reef belong to the hotels: Sunrise Diamond Beach Resort-Select, Royal Grand Sharm and Vera Club. The beaches are small but wonderful. Their sand is medium beauty. The seabed is rocky. Everywhere, about 50-100 meters from the coast, the depth is almost the same. About 40-70 cm. It is highly dependent on tides. Access to the coral reef is easy on the pontoons. Coral reef is nice, but relatively uniform. It is an almost vertical wall with beautiful coral. The wall ranges from 7 to 15 meters. Then the bottom is relatively rocky and the depth increases sharply. The slope of the coral wall is at an angle of 80-90 degrees. Snorkeling is like swimming parallel to the wall. Despite the beautiful coral wall, snorkeling itself is very monotonous. Just a wall overgrown with nice coral, after which the depth becomes significant. Snorkeling here is not suitable for weak swimmers or people who are afraid of the deep. Expect a gentle sea current, parallel to the shore, with a frequently changing direction. Better swimmers can extend their snorkeling area to the north as well as to the south. There are a lot of pontoons in both directions, where they can relax if needed. The beach is not protected by the north and east winds prevailing in the winter. Expect most of the beach to be exposed to these winds. Often the wind raises wind waves and is not very pleasant for snorkeling.

The wild beach area to the Harbor is pretty dirty. When a strong North or Northwest wind blows, the beach is sheltered and is a good alternative. The coral reef in front of the beach is not something special. Rating 4-5. To the right of the beach looking to the sea, the coral reef is a bit better. Rating 5-6. The depth around the wall of the coral reef is on average 2-3-4 meters. In places a little more. The bottom beneath the coral wall is light sand and small coral islands. The area is good for snorkeling of inexperienced people.

White Knight Reef Beaches belong to the hotels:  Hilton Sharks Bay Resort,  Concorde El Salam Hotel,  Island View Resort and Royal Savoy Sharm El Sheikh. The cleanliness of their beaches is kept well. The sand is the best in front of  Island View Resort and Royal Savoy Sharm El Sheikh.  Evaluation 8. Not so good in front of a Hilton Sharks Bay Resort.  Evaluation 6. White Knight Coral Reef is wonderful. Best is in front of a Hilton Sharks Bay Resort and Concorde El Salam Hotel, The underwater landscape of the coral reef across the bay is the same. After a shallow coral plateau (0.5m), there follows a coral wall with a height of 4 to 8 meters. Below the coral wall, the seabed is a mixture of light sand and various coral formations. This second plateau beneath the coral wall, where the depth is from 4 to 8 meters, is wide from 10 to 30-50 meters. Perfect snorkeling area! The marine fauna here is perhaps the most abundant in the whole area of Sharm El Sheikh. The bay is relatively well protected from winds, which is also important for good snorkeling. In the northern part of the bay in front of Siva Sharm Resort, the coral reef is also very good. For the good swimmers, the two reefs to the north - Ras Bob (Montazah Public Beach) and Ras Nasrani are also a good alternative to snorkeling. Their characteristics and quality are similar.

Located just northwest of the beach at Unawatuna, Jungle Beach is a tiny, semi-hidden bay surrounded by jungle. A coral reef is located just a few meters out from the beach. The reef and snorkeling begin only 30 feet away from the beach, directly in front. The reef at Jungle Beach is basically dead, however, you'll still encounter plenty of small marine life.   You can also snorkel around the rocks on both sides of the bay, but beware of waves pushing you too close to the sharp edges. Under normal conditions, the current isn't an issue. Waves typically aren't sizable at Jungle Beach, but always be mindful of the basic safety rules for snorkeling. Along with schools of colorful fish and reef dwellers, you may also encounter crabs, moray eels, trigger fish, parrot fish, barracudas, and maybe even a turtle.

Nice beach covered with a mixture of sand and pebbles. Crystalline sea water, but at times quite dirty. Very crowded in the summer. Good snorkeling and swimming, kayaking. The ancient city of Butrint, UNESCO's site, is just behind Saranda. It is easy to combine a beach with a cultural walk in antiquity.

The island is small. Easily walks on foot. Its western part, where the harbor is, is overcrowded. Relatively more peaceful in the south and west. The best coral reef is in the northeast. Best to snorkel at high tide, otherwise you will have to walk out a long way across rocks and coral to water that is deep enough to swim/snorkel in. There are many dumps in many places.
Gili Meno is the most untouched Gili island, and it has the finest beaches and best snorkeling waters of all the Gilis. No contest. Best snorkeling spots-top NE and NW corners

The circumference of Gili Air island is travelable by foot in around two hours. Beach bungalows, restaurants and shops line the entire east coast of the island, while the more desolate west coast offers better beaches. Best snorkeling-east side from near the top.

Drymades Beach Albania Almost a wild beach. Crystal clear water. Turquoise color. The beach is white pebbles. Beautiful views of the mountain from the sea. The beach is not crowded. There are sun loungers and umbrellas. Camping.

Semi-wild beach. Crystal clear sea, deep blue water. Pleasant temperatures throughout the year. A fairly wide beach with particles of gravel and white pebbles. The beach is surrounded by beautiful mountains. The place is not clean. Chairs and sun beds are rented.

Big beach. Very clean sea water. The beach is a mixture of gravel and sand. Bars with good and cheap food. Large parking. Lounges and parking 500 lek. I do not recommend a walk from Himara to the beach - it's far away, there is no shadow, no gravel road. Just by car.There are campsites.
Beautiful place. Incredible panorama and great snorkeling.Overcrowded beach. The area is not kept clean.
Here you can feel nature. Lovely secluded beach. There are no crowds because it is not easy to reach him. It's about twenty minutes down a dirt road. There is a beach bar. I recommend camping.

Jimbaran beach - the place is not at all quiet. In the central and southern parts of it are crocheted cafes and restaurants, there are many sun loungers and umbrellas on the shoreline. Further north, the situation is changing - sun loungers are hidden in green spaces, tourists are much smaller. The sand is light yellow, strong and pleasant, although it is generally dirty on the beach. The water in the sea is clean, despite the fact that there are constant waves. You can swim, but you can hardly swim safely. It is good only in the southernmost part of Jimbaran beach, where it is covered with a cape. The beach is more suitable for beginners surfers and walks. After lunch, closer to sunset, the beach is even more lively - tourists are filled with fish restaurants, goes for a walk and the local population.
A crowded beach in the summer. Pebble beach. Very clear sea water. Turquoise blue sea. Good snorkeling - lots of fish. Silky music from the pubs. Dear food.

The length of Sanur beach is about five kilometers. The sand is everywhere yellow, sometimes very large, similar to millet. Sanur beach can be divided into 2 parts, northern and southern. North - quieter, southern with more tourist. Sanur's beach in the northern part is not very crowded, except for the evenings of the days off, when the local people come to rest on the beach. But the Balinese tuslyat in the northern part of the beach, to the south of them there is almost no. Soft waves - you can swim. Strong tides. No sun beds near the water. Actually, there are sunbeds, but they are concentrated near the hotels, some distance from the coastline.
Wild beach. Only time by sea. Beautiful nature.

A beach with gray volcanic sand and a bunch of boats on the beach. The whole coast is strewn with rubbish. In the sea, garbage is not much less. A beach with gray volcanic sand and a bunch of boats on the beach. The whole coast is strewn with rubbish. In the sea, garbage is not much less. The beach is crowded. A lot of tourists go to Lovina, that would look at the dolphins.

Dirty, busy, dirty. Rubbish on the beach, it is heavily littered.  Garbage floating in the water and on the shore. You cannot walk more than two meters without getting perpetually hassled by beach vendors trying to sell you a seat or a drink.

Beautiful white soft sand, clear blue waters that are warm and inviting. It's like a little lagoon with no waves and stays shallow for a long way out giving you the confidence that it's more than safe to relax in the waters. Little fish can be seen darting about.  If you have small children, this beach is for you. For an adult which likes to swim it is quite boring. The dearest place near the fence is up to the chest. Some places are full with the seagrass, that is why morning swim following the beach will not really work. Only the sections next to the major resorts are relatively clean.  Beach cleaners from the surrounding hotels are constantly raking up washed up seaweed and keeping this beach pristine.  Sections of the beach are very dirty with lots of debris. The only annoyance is the 'lookie, lookie' sales men and women regularly stopping to sell you their wares, but they are friendly and polite and do move on. Wind surfing, parasailing & kayaking all available and great fun , all the hotel beach bars welcome in non residence which allows you to sample what they have on offer. No waves at all (because of the coral reef belt surrounding the area in the distance), but there is at times a strong current (strong enough to make standing still on your feet difficult) flowing along the coast line from right to left so be careful.  Many beautiful fishes in the water and sea creature, inhabitants of the relative dead coral reef! You just need to swim maybe some 20-30 metres away from the shore to find them (and the water will be still up to your neck only). The paved walkway from one end to the other links some beautiful properties, all open for guests, not for locals!

Traditional Bali busy beach, where you can daily observed fisherman life and hundred colorful fishing boats, with magic view on Amed Volcano and beautify reef just of the stone coast. Bear in mind that it is not a sandy beach (it is stone type of beach). Good coral, interesting underwater landscape, and good snorkelling for both learners and experienced snorkellers.

The beach is dirty with gray sand, murky waters and quite a fair bit of litter, like plastic wrappers, rice packets and random bits and pieces lying around. Some areas are full of the local fishing fleet boats and it is very busy.

Great little beach. Mix between white & black sand.  Some facilities: A few shacks around for drinks.  Snorkeling area is just 50 - 100 meters from the beach. Soft and hard coral, and also many fish species. Be careful with the current, its quite strong.

A small, narrow beach in a deep bay. The sand is of average quality. Cleanliness is not maintained well enough. It's not too crowded. Often in the bay there are many boats. Underwater there are minimal conditions for mediocre snorkeling.

The sea is very clean. The water is in blue to turquoise. In the middle   of the beach there is a great rock you can climb. The beach is a   combination of small stones and sand. The beach is reached by a dirt road that is not very long. There is a parking lot for cars, the fee is 100 light. For an umbrella and two sun loungers, the fee is 700 light. There are restaurants. A very beautiful place, but very crowded. Too many people in one place.

Great location, ideal for those seeking tranquility!  It is a large beach structured in small coves that offer a sea of ​​beautiful colors. Place really pristine and in fact is not very crowded. Beach with fine white sand.  The cedar forest provides shade and protection from the sun and the sea is very clear! Ideal location for campers who respect nature and do not cause damage to the environment when staying there! Too bad for so many abandoned garbage everywhere and the remains ... "organic" human spread where you least expect the usual ignorant, uncivilized and rude, because of the total absence, of course, the beach services. There are no facilities (bar, sun baths) so plan.
Nice beach with river and palm trees.
NULL
The beach is huge, with crystal waters. Some places on the beach are more crowded, but there are also secluded ones. There are many restaurants and hotels in the area. Beautiful panorama.

Typical city beach. Narrow and sometimes overcrowded. The beach is nestled with a mixture of pebbles and sand. Crystal clear water. At first the sea is shallow at a great distance from the coast. At higher waves there is no visibility in the water. There are many restaurants.

This is the most noisy, crowded and tusovic beach of Benidorm. Along the whole beach is a beautiful promenade. Along the embankment are bars, cafes, restaurants, coffee shops and snack bars, as well as supermarkets, small shops, souvenir shops, hotels and apartments. Light and bright sand. The beach is cleaned daily, in the morning the sand is leveled. Comfortable sandy entrance to the sea.

The beach is cleaned daily, the sand is leveled. The entrance to the sea is gentle, the depth does not come at once, the bottom is sandy. Sea water is clean and transparent. The beach has all the necessary infrastructure. Along the whole beach stretches a beautiful promenade, an excellent place for evening walks and recreation. There is a bicycle path.
City beach covered with pebbles and sand. Pure water. but at times quite cloudy. Strong music from the pubs. Umbrella with two sunbeds costs 800 light.
Typical city beach. Narrow and sometimes overcrowded. The beach is nestled with a mixture of pebbles and sand. Crystal clear water. There are many restaurants.
Пляж представляет собой небольшую естественную бухту, с обеих сторон окруженную скалистыми выступами. На пляже песок, вперемешку с камнями и валунами. Дно скалистое, морская вода прозрачная и чистая.
Stony white beach, divided by a river that descends from the mountains above. The beach is calm. The sunset here is magnificent. There are restaurants, a hotel and a camping.

La Mata Beach-It is considered the best beach in Torrevieja, it is the longest and widest. Two kilometers of the beach strip are completely covered with fine and soft sand of light yellow color. Rest on this beach come, both tourists and local residents.  The beach is cleaned daily, the sand is leveled. Along the sea line, in some places there is a natural debris carried ashore by a sea wave, but it does not interfere. The water in the sea is clean and transparent, the entrance is shallow, the bottom is sandy. Along the entire beach lies a long pedestrian promenade. From the west and east, La Mata is surrounded by natural reserves and dunes.

The beach of Los Locos (Playa de Los Locos) - one of the central urban beaches of Torrevieja. Located this beach in the eastern part of the coast of Torrevieja (north of the center) and finds a little distant from the historic center of the city, at a distance, about a half kilometers. Nevertheless, the beach Lokos is very visited, and is one of the favorite places for beach recreation among the guests of the city. In the high holiday season on the beach is crowded, it is almost impossible to find a secluded place. On the beach Lokos, mostly fine sand of light color, sometimes interspersed with small stones. In the eastern (northern) part of the beach is rounded in the form of a small bay, and borders with the rocky coast of the cape. On the west side, the beach of Los Lokos is bordered by the Cala del Palagre (Cala del Palagre). The stony bay of Palangre, territorially refers to the beach of Lokos, visually the bay flows smoothly into the sandy beach strip. In the bay is mainly rocky rocks, in the center of the coastline sand is light gray. Log into the sea is not very convenient, at the bottom there are rocky rocks.
The beach in Durres, a 10-kilometer beach on the Adriatic. The Blue Sea, fine sand and beach bars make Durres an attractive destination for both local and foreigners.
White sand, clean seawater, evergreen pine create a very exciting harmony.

The long main beach itself is the busiest swimming beach on the island. Beach with white, soft sand. Pure sea water.  There is an abundance of sea life and corals. Check little peninsula in the centre of the beach. Long Beach is destination for large groups of tourists (mainly Chinese) on package tours. It is overcrowded.  Trashes you can see along the beach or nearby some resorts (plastics, bottles, most of it are cigarette butts and cigarette boxes)
Nice long beach. Very good soft sand. The coral reef, which is about 100 meters away from the beach, is mediocre.

6 kilometers of nice sandy beach with promenade and palm trees. Very quiet and clean place. but the water is very dirty. If you look at Google Earth, you will see 3 or 4 rivers flowing into the sea across the beach that carry junk. There are several restaurants, hotels and pine trees on the beach. I recommend for families with young children.

A nice snorkeling place, but too many people. It is a family snorkeling spot. The fish are abundant. Corals are very good. for snorkeling,  The beach and water are littered with plastic and wrappers. This

Beautiful beach, overlooking Corfu. The sand is mainly of small pebbles. Cleanliness: rather clean, but there are places with junk. The beach is hardly a dirt road. The price of an umbrella and two sun loungers is 700 lek per day.
Beach accessible only by car. A small beach. Rocky. Sea water is very clean. Everywhere is occupied by umbrellas and sun loungers. Umbrella and two sun loungers 600 light. There is a restaurant.

The coastline is entirely occupied by resorts, most of which are in the democratic price segment. Almost all of the Resort are separated from the sea wall thick mangroves, through a rather narrow passageways that cut through the sea, Just behind the mangrove strip follows a narrow strip of sand, into the tide flooded with water, and a low retaining wall, behind which are variously arranged bungalows in the shade of the trees. Walk along the entire Pangalisan Beach along the shore is impossible even in the strongest outflow, this is hampered by mangroves and areas of rocks outstanding in the sea. Almost all tourists come here for snorkeling and diving. About 2 kilometers long coral reef. Reef Basics: Depth: 5 - 35m Visibility: 15 - 25m Currents: Usually gentle but can be strong A shifting current usually shakes the place; it can randomly run northwards or southwards. Swimming against it can be exhausting.
Long, sandy beach. The beach itself is not interesting. There are several resorts. There is the usual steep drop-off/wall about 100m from the beach. This site offers a  large cracks everywhere.

Siladen Island is a small island surrounded by a beautiful white sandy beach.  It is entirely fringed by coral reefs offering fabulous coral drop-offs where soft corals, sea anemones and sponges thrive.

Wonderful Island - needs attention for rubbish. The beaches does have a very fine white sand that is very comfortable on the feet. Plastic waste and disposable nappies that constantly float onto the shore line. The island is  crowded - and no so good great snorkeling. The visibility - not ideal. 4-8m. Underwater landscape is unspectacular.  The best stuff is in the southeastern part of the island.

The island is beautiful it just needs to be maintained. A lot of trash around the beach and in the water. plastic water bottles everywhere on the beach and in the ocean.  Snorkelling is  mediocre. Crowded.
Pretty but crowded island. The beach is a bit dirty. Average quality snorkeling.
Nice sandy beach with pristine white sand, clear water and shady trees.
This beach is probably the most popular of the Pangkor beaches. Maybe it is because it is so close to Pangkor Town. The water is shallow and not so clear.

The sand is a mixture of pebbles and coarse sand. The beach is full of sun loungers and umbrellas. The water is very clean. The landscape is very beautiful, rocky shores and lagoons in the rocks. The beach at times is crowded. A small place to swim. Many hiking boats stopped.
One of the best beaches in Thailand. Wonderful sand. Incredible color of sea water. Underwater, it is mostly plain sandy bottom and uninteresting.

Very narrow and pebbly beach, but with a beautiful view. Crystal clear water, but the bottom is with stones. A lot of fish. Pretty snorkel. The gulfs are reached on very steep steps. For an umbrella with two sun loungers, the fee is 7 euros. The place is very crowded.
Good sand. Many boats stop in the middle of the beach. Crowded. Mediocre small coral reef south of the beach.

Donald Duck Bay Beach is one of Thailand’s best. Sure gets crowded when the daytrippers hit  it. Water tends to be crystal clear and all those rocks off the beach attract a good array of fishies.  Mediocre corals.  Good sand. Many boats stop in the middle of the beach. Crowded. Camping in the national park is good.
Beach on the harbor. Very overcrowded. The beach is a mixture of stones and coarse sand. The water is transparent. It's snorkeling.
A small white sandy beach. Trees with nice shade. Small Coral Reef. Terms of average quality snorkeling.

Access to Romantic Beach is by boat (or swimming) only and is occasionally a stopping point on daytrip boat itineraries. White coral sand on the beach A good approach to the sea is at once deep and you can swim Mainly flat sandy bottom with broken-up dead coral in the deeper water. About 100m North of Romantic Beach, there is a decent spot of corals-4.5/10.

Wonderful place. Clean sea and clean beach. The beach is entirely sandy. Crystalline water. During the season there are restaurants, 7 euros worth umbrella and two sun loungers. After the season is a wild beach.

Coral Bay is Perhentian Kecil's second most popular beach. Pretty nice sand, not so clear water and a big range of accommodation.  Crowded. A fairly good coral reef is around the rocks north of the bay. The middle of Coral Bay itself isn’t conducive to snorkelling – there’s a fair bit of boat traffic passing; and what coral there is mostly unspectacular
Mira Bay-this place is very appealing - nice sand which extends quite a distance into the water. Relatively good coral reefs are around the rocks north and south of the bay.

Saint Gordes to the south. Long and beautiful beach. Crystal clear water. Sand bottom and stones at the beginning, but then only sand. There are showers, sun loungers, umbrellas and a free beach area. Umbrellas and two sun loungers cost 5 euros.

Long Beach is about 1km stretch of wite sand. It is where most of Kecil’s accommodation is.  The whole bay is a mass of daytrip and taxi boats coming and going and it is simply not safe to swim or snorkel here. Sandy seabed.  In the northern part of the bay there is a mediocre coral reef. Accordingly, snorkeling is not much of a quality.
One of the best beaches on the Perthian Islands Perfect flat sand Perfect approach to the sea There is a ten minute walking trail to it from D’Lagoon Resort.
The beach  and  the sand are with  a medium quality.  The coral reef /Shark Point/ at the southern end of the bay is relatively good.
Beautiful bay.  In the southernmost part of the bay, the coral reef is the best. There is also a camping site.
A nice beach with several resorts. Good sand. Only a few meters from the beach there is a coral reef.
A nice beach with several resorts. Good sand. Wonderful coral garden, about 100m offshore from the Reef  Chalets and Coral View Island Resort.
Santa Barbara Beach Sandy beach, wide, long and very clean! Beautiful water. Upon entering, the seabed gradually becomes deeper. Good snorkeling. Many tourists visit it.

Wonderful bay. A nice sandy strip. The seabed is almost everywhere ideal sand. At the northern end of the bay there is a good coral reef. The Bay is the top location in the Perhentians for turtle sightings.
Lovely beach with perfect sand. The seabed is almost everywhere ideal sand. In the northeastern part of the beach there are mediocre corals.
Nice beach with perfect sand. The seabed is almost everywhere ideal sand. The water is very cloudy.
Nice beach. Less people come over.  Not very clean environment, sadly.

A wonderful place to relax, swim, walk and enjoy. It is one of the few beaches where plenty of shady places are available. It is located on the edge of national park - a great place for hiking. If you want to stay here at night, campus are available on rent. You can reach the beach either by walking from National Park main entry or by boating.

Not the best beach for sure, it's more of a harbor for speed boats from Sanur Beach. It has a potential, but it's quite dirty. An excess of tourism. The beach is divided by a rock. On the one side are a lot of boats but if you go to the other side of the rock there is more relaxed. A nice coral reef, but the place is not suitable for snorkeling due to the large boat traffic.

Marathias Beach Wide sandy beach, which is not very well maintained. Two lounges and umbrella cost 5 euros. Not too crowded - except for Sunday when local residents come. Sandy bottom with small rocks.
Beach St. George Argirades Very long sandy beach. For lovers of nature. It is not overpopulated.
Small beach and pretty crowdy. Gorgeous scenery. The beach itself depending on the day can be easy to swim in and clean but on other days can be rough with waves, undercurrent and trash washing up.

BEACH ISSOS Very long, wide, sandy beach. Desert landscape. There are dunes between the sea and the lake. Pure water. The bottom is quite shallow and therefore suitable for children. It is not crowded. A windy area for surf, kite and windsurfing. Umbrella and 2 sun loungers, 5 or 6 euros for the whole day.
The island is lovely and has no crowds. Sandy white beached. No garbage in water nor in sand. Goog snorkeling.

The water is clear, sand is soft. No rubbish in the water. Gili Nanggu has an impressive array of fishes and the corals are beautiful too. Since it is quite shallow, it will be easy for beginners to enjoy the snorkeling experience. No currents.

The beach of Tulamben is covered with large black pebbles that make it very difficult to walk. Nice spot for snorkeling and diving  Rich underwater marine life, and fantastic ship wreck. The US Liberty wreck: entering the water from the black pebble beach can be quite difficult, but after about 30 meter you reach the black volcanic sand. The wreck lies on a sandy slope parallel to the shore, roughly southeast (stern) to northwest (bow). Part of the superstructure is close to the surface (about 5m) and can also be reached by snorkelers. The wreck is about 120m long, the deepest point is around 30m and it is nicely covered with corals and sponges.  Paradise Reef (or patch reef) and the River: the River is a great place to do muck diving and find rare animals such as the harlequin and the robust ghost pipefish, several species of eels and even the mimic octopus, boxer crabs or the harlequin shrimp!  Tulamben Drop Off: about 500 m to the east of the wreck and close to the temple, the underwater wall drops to a depth of 60m (the top is around 3 to 5 m).  Batu Klebit: this dive site southeast of Tulamben beach. There are some rocks close to the shore, around which you can dive, and some large reefs a bit offshore. You dive on a slope with nice hard and soft corals and sandy areas in between.
Nice beach with white sand and not so crowded. Clear water and good snorkelling close to the shore.

Nice beach with a fair admission fee (35 for adults).  It is clean and not much people. You can snorkel or dive here with a great view of the coral reefs with many different kind of fishes.   Lifeguards are always on duty and keep you safe!
The beach is very nice and clean.  You can make diving or snorkeling with dolphins with instructors.
Best place to snorkel and dive in Aqaba. Beautiful reefs. You will be amazed with the ship and the tank about 10 meter deep. Showers and umbrellas available for free
The beach is a mixture of sand and stones. It is well maintained by the staff of the surrounding hotels. Good coral reef. North and south of the beach the snorkeling conditions are even better.

The bay is maybe 150m in diameter, wrapped around by a gorgeous beach for guests only. The bay is surrounded by rocky hills, only open to the sea. This gives a wonderful protection against the cold and strong winds which are typical for the Red Sea in winter time. Great snorkeling spot, with a wide variety of corals and fish, although you have to swim away from the shore to see them.
Wind-protected beaches. They are well maintained by adjacent hotels. Makadi Palace, Makadi Spa and Grand Makadi. The reef in front of those hotels is  perfect.

The central beaches of Makadi Bay begin from Fort Arabesque to the north, to Cleopatra Luxury to the south. It is difficult to summarize their qualities. They are generally well maintained by the adjoining hotels. Entrance into the water in some places is without problems, others quite rocky and coral. The northern beaches are well protected from the wind.  There is a nice coral reef in front of Fort Arabesque.
Well maintained beaches from their adjoining hotels. Good sand. A hard entrance to the water. Very good snorkeling.

One of the largest and most beautiful beaches in southern Corfu. Very fine sand, clean water. The place is windy, going for surfing. The lake and the dunes make this place very natural and wild. I recommend.

A lovely sandy beach stretching for 3 miles from Kalamaki to Laganas, the home of the Carretta turtle. It slopes so gently into the sea that you could walk out for ages and the sea would stillness only be up to your waist. Clean sandy beach.Great for relaxing walk. Very warm sea... can go out quite a way before it gets deep, fishes swimming around your feet and legs...
Laganas is one of the major party areas of Zakynthos. Laganas Beach is busy and  overcrowded.  Rubbish everywhere and fag ends in the sand along the beach.

Really beautiful and unspoiled golden sand beach, clear warm water. It's a surrounded by cliffs of sandstone and that makes the beach feel like a hidden treasure. Mainly stones where the sunbeds are  Good snorkelling at either ends of the beach.
Lovely sand / pebble beach with amazing blue sea. The beach  is  a little pebbled as you enter the waterq but herw is one of the best locations on the island for snorkelling.

Very nice, wide and clean beach. Good with kids as it's quite shallow water for quite a bit of distance. The beach is about 1500m long and slopes gently into the sea. The water sports centre is off to the side - paragliding, jet skis, canoes and more, and do not interfere with the beach, so it is safe for children.

Best place to go if you're a beach lover; the color of water is unreal of blue and the abandoned wreck on the beach creates a very beautiful picture. The beach can only be seen from the top of the cliff and and if you want to reach it go to an 1 day cruise because you'll see navagio and another amazing virgin beaches from the island.  The image of blue water and golden sand blends perfectly so do not miss the opportunity to take some beautiful pictures.
Nice sandy beach, blue sea, plenty of bars with waiter/waitress service to the beach. Not too crowded. Views to mainland Greece and Kefalonia.

Koroni Beach Type-sand and pebbles Size-medium long but large Facilities - is not equipped for tourists Food-There is a small bar on the beach for drinks and snacks  Description the road to get to Koroni beach is unpaved and not suitable for all cars. The beach is very nice and the sea is really stunning here. The shades of colors that you see coming from above the beach are breathtaking. The stretch of coast on the left is all made of clay and then you can also put the mud all over your face or all over the body. We must get the mud on the body and wait for it to dry and then have a swim in the sea to clean up. The result is an extremely smooth skin.

Kaminia Beach Type-sand Size-together are up to 2 km long. While Kaminia is approximately 25 meters large, Potamakia is almost 80 meters. Facilities-Kaminia has several points with loungers and umbrellas for rent and Potamakia only one, upon the arrival of the road Food-along the beach of Kaminia there are a few bars while there are none in Potamakia Description Kaminia Potamakia together are the southern beaches of the island of Kefalonia. While the first is bordered by a narrow road to park and has several points where you can rent deck chairs, the second you can walk further along the beach Kaminia and is free. Kaminia also called Mounda is perhaps the only remaining beach in Kefalonia nesting turtles Caretta-Caretta.  For this reason, there are a couple of rules to follow to protect the species; do not make holes or dig, it is forbidden to camp, light fires, and even walking around at night in the summer.

Mytros beach is stunning with tirquase crystal clear waters! Consists of pure white pebbles which is hard to walk.  Beach shoes help walk on the pebbles!.  Facilities-there are sun beds and umbrellas for rent and showers right in the middle of the beach Food-there is a bar on the beach and in the high season some trailer that serves as bar It’s surrounded by high cliffs and there is only one road that from the village of Divarata will lead you down to Myrtos bay. The beach is huge and therefore the areas free of deck chairs are many, even if it is crowded in August. The sea has a depth that degrades very quickly and at the left end of the beach there are also a cave where you can pass through. There are also panoramic spots, going on the coastal road to Assos, where you can admire the beach as a whole. Myrtos has the sunset right in front and then if you stay late at the beach you can also enjoy the calm sea and the shades of pink in the sky. Another peculiarity is that the sea a bit 'rough water becomes an almost electric fluorescent blue.

Petani beach is one of the best beaches in Kefalonia. Light Blue water seems like swimming pool.  Wide beach in two parts. Main part sandy/pebbly with beds and parasols available. Plenty of other space to choose though. Right side of the beach is divided by a rocky outcrop but did provide some lovely little coves with some shaded areas. Sea access is tricky but shoes did help. Water clear and warm. Beach shelved steeply but provided a lovely swimming area.
Pebbles not sand.  Beach shoes recommended. Pure sea water. Good snorkeling.
Nice and clean beach with tons is restaurants and amenities. Taverna, parking, sunbeds, shower and toilets. Good for snorkling.
Sandy pebble beach. The water is shallow in most parts and becomes deeper gradually. Pure water.
The beach is surrounded by many pines and rocks in the sea. Summer is very crowded.

This is really a must see location! The area is part of the national park with an organised car park due to its popularity which has charges for motorized transport so my advice is use the local bus service which takes you right into the area. The beaches are white sand, turquoise coloured seas with shallow waters, some beach areas are organised with sun beds & shades as well as a selection of places to eat and drink (but can be very expensive!) The area can get very busy as expected with day visitors from Ibiza but continue walking and the crowds thin out and the views get better!
